  "prompt": "What is the salary of a Scientific Officer in BARC?",
  "response": "The salary of a Scientific Officer at the Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC) can vary based on the specific position, level of experience, and other factors. Generally, Scientific Officers are classified under various grades, and their pay scales may also differ.\n\nAs of my last knowledge update, the starting salary for a Scientific Officer (depending on their qualifications) could be in the range of \u20b967,700 (Level 10) to higher depending on the level of the position. There can also be additional benefits, allowances, and opportunities for promotion that can significantly influence total compensation.\n\nFor the most accurate and current information, it is best to refer to the official BARC website or their latest recruitment notifications.",
